                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Fine miniatures, borders, diagrams, historiated initials.
            Rewritten inscription as written 'in alma urbe in 1383', fol. 36v. (P&amp;A ii.
            128, pl. XII)
                        <list type="gloss">
                           <head>fol. 1r</head>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">initial M</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">Macrobius, holding open book.</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">miniature</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">Three scenes. Scipio, with a sword and long cloak, and
                  King Masinissa, in a crown, long robe and cloak, stand next to one another
                  conversing. King Masinissa looks up at a semicircular diagram, showing the
                  heavenly spheres. Scipio and King Masinissa seated on a long decorated seat,
                  conversing.</seg>
                           </item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="gloss">
                           <head>fol. 1v</head>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">miniature</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">Scipio asleep in bed, his sword placed by his side,
                  supports with one hand a circle of spheres. In the centre of the circle are
                  Rome and Carthage, surrounded by the Milky Way. Against it are three sets of
                  figures, showing Scipio embracing his father; speaking to his grandfather,
                  Scipio Africanus; and conversing with both of them together.</seg>
                           </item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="gloss">
                           <head>fol. 3r</head>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">miniature</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">Macrobius writing at desk, next to an open cupboard
                  with books, lying flat on shelves. On the desk is a circular stand with two
                  open books.</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Type</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="genreform">initial C</seg>
                           </item>
                           <label>Subject</label>
                           <item>
                              <seg type="subject">Head-and-shoulders portrait of a young
                  man.</seg>
                           </item>
                        </list>
